### Auth module — manual verification
### Requires: API running (npm run dev:api), Postgres + Redis reachable.
### Tip (VS Code REST Client): {{login.response.body.$.data.accessToken}} chains tokens.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api
@email = test@example.com
@password = password123

### Register a customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "name": "Test Customer",
  "role": "CUSTOMER"
}

### Register a seller (the seller app sends role=SELLER)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "seller@example.com",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "name": "Test Seller",
  "role": "SELLER"
}

### Reject ADMIN self-registration (should 400 validation error)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "evil@example.com",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "name": "Nope",
  "role": "ADMIN"
}

### Verify email with OTP (copy the 6-digit code from the email / Redis)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "otp": "123456"
}

### Resend OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/resend-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### Login (sets refresh cookie, returns accessToken)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Refresh (uses the httpOnly refresh cookie set by login)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh

### Forgot password (sends reset OTP)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### Reset password (with OTP from email / Redis)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "otp": "123456",
  "password": "newpassword123"
}

### Logout (needs access token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.data.accessToken}}

### Google OAuth — open in a browser, not the REST client
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/google
